<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - FUEL INJECTION PUMP - REASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="19">
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>In-Chassis</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new O-Ring onto injection pump hub. Lubricate O-Ring before installing injection
                    pump. Mount the injection pump to the engine front cover plate mounting studs. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051127">11.27</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Be sure that the timing pin tool (ZTSE4372) is positioned through the hub and into the
                            timing plate. Finger-tighten until timing pin contacts the hub. DO NOT ROTATE ENGINE WITH
                            TIMING PIN INSTALLED. Rotating the engine will damage the timing pin and timing plate.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>Verify that the engine #1 cylinder is on the compression stroke (TDC). Also verify static
                            timing by checking the timing mark on pulley and marks on timing plate. Refer to "Set
                            Injection Pump to Engine Timing Prior to Pump Removal" in this section for a detailed
                            procedure.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position injection pump drive gear slot so that four of the five kidney slotted holes
                    align with mounting holes on the injection pump and timing pin tool is aligned in center of fifth
                    kidney slotted hole. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051128">11.28</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1"></para>
                <figure id="ef1051127" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3078" filename="../figeg3/EG3078.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11.27.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Timing Pin Tool Bracket</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Timing Pin Tool</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Fuel Injection Pump</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Mounting Stud (4)</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Front Cover</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1051128" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3083" filename="../figeg3/EG3083.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11.28.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Timing Pin Tool</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Drive Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Front Cover</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Upper Idler Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Timing Mark, Upper Idler Gear and Cam Shaft Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. Timing Mark, Upper Idler Gear and Lower Idler Gear</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Position bolts in the center of the kidney slotted holes. The pump drive gear may be
                            rotated by lifting and turning to position.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure injection pump to front cover with four nuts and tighten to the special torque
                    value. (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051129">11.29</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and tighten the four capscrews securing the injection pump gear to the injection
                    pump at the special torque value. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051130">11.30</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1051129" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3075" filename="../figeg3/EG3075.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11.29.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Fuel Injection Pump</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Front Cover</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Mounting Nut (4)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1051130" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3084" filename="../figeg3/EG3084.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11.30.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Drive Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Mounting Bolt (4)</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Fifth Kidney Hole</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Front Cover</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Timing Pin Tool</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove timing pin tool from the gear/hub.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the injection pump drive gear access cover using a new O-Ring as follows: Refer
                    to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051131">11.31</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install a new O-Ring onto the access cover slot and lubricate.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Secure the access cover to front cover using the three capscrews. Tighten capscrews
                        to special torque value. See Appendix.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the injection pump tail support bracket as follows: (
                    <emph type="bold">Refer to Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051132">11.32</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    )
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install bolt, washer, nut and throttle cable bracket for the fuel injection pump.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the two bolts mounting the throttle bracket to the bottom of the fuel pump
                        and tighten to special torque value.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the engine side bracket to cylinder block and snug bolts. Torque bolt
                        between brackets to special torque value.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the two crankcase bolts to special torque value.</para>
                    <figure id="ef1051131" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg1799" filename="../figeg1/EG1799.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 11.31.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Access Cover</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Bolt</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Front Cover</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1051132" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3080" filename="../figeg3/EG3080.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 11.32.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Throttle Cable Bracket</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Throttle Bracket</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Throttle Bracket Nut</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. Engine Side Bracket Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. Throttle Bracket Mounting</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. Engine Side Bracket</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation Of Electric Shut-off Solenoid</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removed, install the electric shut-off solenoid as follows:
                    <emph type="bold">(Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051133">11.33</hotlnk>)
                    </emph>
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the solenoid and bracket assembly onto the injection pump mounting studs.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Assemble the metri-pack connector to the wiring harness.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Adjustment Of Electric Shut-off Solenoid Injection Pump (Refer to Figure 11.32).</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The adjustment procedure must be completed as specified to prevent solenoid burn-out or
                        internal damage to the injection pump.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set parking brake, put transmission in neutral and depress clutch, if applicable.
                    <emph type="bold">DO NOT DEPRESS THE ACCELERATOR PEDAL AT THIS TIME!</emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn keyswitch to "
                    <emph type="bold">START"</emph>
                    position to engage starter/pull in E.S.O.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After starter is engaged fully, depress accelerator pedal to provide starting fuel
                    quantity.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to vehicle Operator's Manual for additional starting instructions.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If engine still does not refer EGES-110, DT 408, DT 466 and International(r) 530 Engine
                    Diagnostic Manual*.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">*- Manual specified witrh latest revision.</emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1051133" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg15237" filename="../figcg1/CG15237.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11.33.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the lube oil supply line as follows: (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051134">11.34</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the protective cap at the crankcase oil outlet elbow and the pump oil
                        inlet.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install a new rubber sealing sleeve at the compression nut end of the tube.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Fasten the tube to the crankcase oil outlet tube and tighten the nut.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Using new copper gaskets, fasten the banjo fitting to the pump oil inlet with the
                        hollow screw at the special torque value.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the fuel filter header as follows: ( Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051135">11.35</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .)
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Insert the header at the crankcase mounting pad. Fasten the header using the two
                        mounting bolts and washers.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the fasteners to the standard torque (see
                        <emph type="bold">Appendix</emph>).
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Be sure to install the throttle cable spring bracket on the mounting bolts which
                                attach the filter header.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove nylon cap above fuel strainer and observe check ball. If check ball is not in
                        this location, priming pump will not work.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1051134" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2342" filename="../figeg2/EG2342.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 11.34.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Hollow Screw</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Compression Nut</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Crankcase Elbow</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. Lube Oil Supply Line</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1051135" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2341" filename="../figeg2/EG2341.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 11.35.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Mounting Bolts</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Fuel filter Header</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">. Install the fuel injection pump fuel return to filter header line as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove protective caps from fuel injection pump return and filter header.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">After positioning tube, install with hollow screws and new copper sealing gaskets at
                        pump and header (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051136">11.36</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ). Tighten to special torque value.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">. Install the fuel injection pump inlet supply hose as follows: ( Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051137">11.37</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .)
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove protective caps from fuel injection pump inlet and filter header.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">After positioning tube, install with hollow screws and new copper sealing gaskets at
                        pump and header. Tighten to special torque value.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the fuel line clamp which holds the fuel injection pump inlet hose and fuel
                        return line together.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1051136" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3045" filename="../figeg3/EG3045.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 11.36.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Valve Cover/Inlet Manifold</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Fuel Return Line</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Crankcase</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. Fuel Filter Header</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1051137" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3044" filename="../figeg3/EG3044.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 11.37.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Fuel Filter Header</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Fuel Inlet Port</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">. Install the final fuel filter inlet fuel line as follows (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051138">11.38</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove protective caps from the fuel filter header and supply pump openings.</para>
                    <specpara>
                        <important>
                            <para>FUEL INLET HOSE MUST BE ATTACHED TO CENTER PORT OF FUEL FILTER HEADER. REVERSING THE
                                FUEL LINES WILL REVERSE THE FUEL FLOW FROM THE FUEL FILTER HEADER TO THE INJECTOR PUMP.
                            </para>
                        </important>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the hollow screws and new copper sealing gaskets at fuel filter header and
                        supply pump banjo fittings to connect fuel line. Tighten to special torque value.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">. Install the supply pump inlet fuel line as follows: Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051139">11.39</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove protective caps from fuel filter header and supply pump openings.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the hollow screws and new copper sealing gaskets at the fuel filter header
                        and supply pump banjo fittings to connect fuel line. Tighten to specified torque value.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Twist to install the fuel line clamp which connects the supply pump inlet fuel line
                        and the final fuel filter inlet fuel line together.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Twist to install the fuel line clamp which connects the supply pump inlet fuel line
                        and the lube oil supply line together.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1051138" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg1985" filename="../figeg1/EG1985.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 11.38.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Fuel Supply Pump</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Hollow Screw</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Fuel Filter Header</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. Fuel Filter Inlet Fuel Line</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1051139" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2338" filename="../figeg2/EG2338.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 11.39.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Fuel Filter Header</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Supply Pump Inlet Fuel Line</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Clamp</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. Hollow Screw</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. Fuel Supply Pump</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">. Install the fuel injection line assembly as follows:</para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>PRIOR TO INSTALLING THE FUEL INJECTION LINE ASSEMBLY, CLEAN WITH FILTERED COMPRESSED AIR
                            AND VISUALLY INSPECT FOR CONTAMINATION OR DAMAGE. REPLACE AS REQUIRED.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the protective caps from the lines, nozzles and delivery valve holders at the
                        pump.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the fuel injection line connector nuts at the pump. Tighten to the special
                        torque value using
                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE4380</emph>
                        at the connector nut. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051140">11.40</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Using special tool
                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE4380</emph>, install the six fuel injection line nuts at the nozzles.
                        Tighten each nut to the special torque value. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051141">11.41</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Injection line fittings at the pump and nozzle are frequently over tightened due to
                                the size of the fitting. This swedges the injection line, often partly closing the ends.
                                This alters fuel delivery characteristics, raises injection line pressures and may cause
                                performance problems or injection pump failure. Visually inspect the ends of the
                                injection lines and replace any with swedged or damaged fittings or holes.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                    <figure id="ef1051140" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3087" filename="../figeg3/EG3087.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 11.40.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Torque Wrench</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Nozzle Line Nut</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Delivery Valve Wrench</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. High Pressure Lines</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1051141" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3088" filename="../figeg3/EG3088.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 11.41.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Torque Wrench</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Delivery Valve Wrench</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Nozzle</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. High Pressure Line Nut</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">. Install the aneroid tube as follows: (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051142">11.42</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the protective caps from the intake manifold elbow and the aneroid.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the hollow screws and new copper sealing gaskets at the aneroid and intake
                        manifold.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the screws at each end of the tube to the special torque value.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the inner and outer throttle return springs as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051143">11.43</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1051142" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3042" filename="../figeg3/EG3042.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11.42.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Valve Cover/Intake Manifold</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Hollow Screw</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Aneroid Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Aneroid Elbow</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Aneroid</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1051143" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3043" filename="../figeg3/EG3043.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11.43.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Inner Throttle Spring</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Spring Bracket</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Outer Throttle Spring</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Throttle Control Lever</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">. Install a new primary fuel filter/strainer as follows: Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051144">11.44</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Lubricate the threads of the strainer cover and install a new O-Ring.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install strainer in cover and hand-tighten into fuel filter header.</para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Install strainer with open end toward filter header.</para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">. Install a new fuel filter as follows: (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051145">11.45</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .)
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Lubricate the filter gasket with clean diesel fuel.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten until the gasket touches the filter header.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten by hand an additional 1/2 turn.</para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Do not add fuel to the new filter.</para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">. Install throttle cable or control rod linkage to the control lever and adjust linkage
                    as specified in the operation and maintenance manual.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1051144" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1980" filename="../figeg1/EG1980.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11.44.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Fuel Filter Header</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Strainer</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. O-Ring</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Strainer Cover</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1051145" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1775" filename="../figeg1/EG1775.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11.45.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Fuel Filter Header</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Fuel Filter</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
